Research consistently shows:

# Writing Organization

depends on:

```text id="m7r5qe"
organized thinking
```

Writing is NOT:

```text id="r1e2qe"
random sentences
```

Students learn:

```text id="x8r6qe"
choose topic
→ write topic sentence
→ add supporting details
→ create closing idea
```

This develops:

* organization
* clarity
* communication
* planning
* stronger written expression

This becomes:

# Organized Writing Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p4r1qe"
more sentences
=
better paragraph
```

or:

```text id="u9e7qe"
details
can be unrelated
```

Some may:

```text id="c6r8qe"
list ideas
without organization
```

Example:

students may write:

```text id="k2e5qe"
I like dogs.
Pizza is tasty.
My bike is red.
```

without:

```text id="n5r3qe"
single topic
```

or:

```text id="t7e1qe"
connected details
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="q3r6qe"
idea-organization reasoning
```

For Grade 3:

focus includes:

Paragraph Parts:

* topic sentence
* supporting details
* closing sentence

Writing Skills:

* staying on topic
* logical order
* clear connections

